If I hold down the F5 key to repeatedly step into, eventually Eclipse pops up an
error message that reads, "An internal error occurred during: 'Step Into'." 

The error seems to have no further effect on the debug session. After
acknowledging the error, the debugger appears to operate as usual.

The following is written to the log file:

!MESSAGE An internal error occurred during: "Step Into".
!STACK 0
java.lang.NullPointerException 
at
org.eclipse.debug.internal.ui.actions.AbstractDebugActionDelegate$DebugRequestJob.run(AbstractDebugActionDelegate.java:143)
at org.eclipse.core.internal.jobs.Worker.run(Worker.java:76) 



Here is a program that I've used to reproduce the bug:

public class EndlessLoop {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int i = 0;
        while(true) {
            i++;
        }
    }
}

To reproduce: Put a breakpoint in the loop, and run it. Hold the F5 key down
until you see the error dialog.

I've noticed this with both our proprietary debugger and with the JDT, which
leads me to believe this is bug in the platform.
